{
  "text": "Carter et al. conducted a retrospective evaluation of NHS Health Checks in Leicester, covering 53 000 participants over a five-year period in a multi-ethnic population. [CITATION_1] They found high levels of case-finding, with 30% of participants having a major undiagnosed physiological risk factor -type 2 diabetes, high risk of diabetes, CKD, hypertension and high CVD risk.",
  "citation_candidates": [
